

what JS lang can do n HTML-page in browser ?


   JS programs using 'Web APIs', will bring any dynamic func to web-page.

   Web APIs --> DOM , XHR , Timer , etc...
   
   all Web APIs are implemented by browsers based on w3c standards.
   
   Web APIs abstracts 'JS objects '


	using DOM API
	---------------
	
  --> can create/retreive/update/delete HTML elements
  --> can change element's style.
  --> can change element's attribute values.
  --> can change element's text content.
  --> can handle event's on HTML elements.
  --> can create rich UI-components.
  
  
  using XHR API
  ----------------
  
  --> can communicate with server async , update result in existing page ( AJAX )
  
  HTML-5 APIs
  -------------
  
  a. canvas API
  
  
  --> drawing effects
  
  b. Audio/Video support API
  
  c.  storage API
   
      sessionStorage
      localStorage
      IndexedDB
      OfflineSupport
   
   d. WebWorker API
   
   e. Geo API
   
   f. WebSockets
   
   g. Web GL
   
   etc...
   
   ------------------------------
   
   
   JS-lang
   
   --> single-threaded lang
   --> supports concurrent
   --> Non-blocking
   
   -----------------------------
   
   
   e.g   chrome-browser
   
         a. JS Engine ( v8 )
         
             call-stack
             heap
             
         b. Web APIs  ( DOM , XHR , etc .. )
         
         c. callback/message queue
         
         d. Event-Loop
         
     ------------------------------
     
     
     single-threaded lang --> one call-stack --> one thing
     
     -----------------------------        
   
   
   

HTML,CSS,JS


some limitations using plain-JS

--> browser compatibility.
--> performanace on DOM manipulation. 
--> memory management.
--> too much code for simple oprn.

soln:

--> JS libraries

    jQuery
    
   limitation jquery
   
   --> low-level ( works with DOM )  
   --> tight-coupling b/w View(DOM) and appln behav.
   --> code organization is very difficult.
   
   high-level JS library.
   
   --> knockout JS  based on MVVM
   
